The Prague MDD takes us Wednesday for the first time with the chip
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008, it is written in the history of the Prague Transportation Company the date on which the first passengers enter the metro, the transit and the bus with an electronic bonus in their pockets instead of a paper ticket.
This can be purchased at this moment by almost one hundred thousand people who have the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy the 30-day, 90-day bonus (it will be valid from 1 January 2009) and at the same time load it on their chip card at the info centres and stations of the transport company at the stations of the Metro, Museum, Můstek, Nadraží Holešovice, Andel, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Rajská zhrada, Kačerov and Luka.
Bonuses can be purchased from yesterday on the website of the transport company, www.dpp.cz.
The service, until afternoon, was used by more than four hundred people.
Those who start using the Internet as a form of trade can definitely start to forget about the ticket sales stations at the subway stations, where they had to regularly take a ticket to get out of the car.
The bonus is purchased online, and the Opencard card recharges it in one of the thirteen branches of the Municipal Library.
"In these places, passengers have a window with prepared staff that helps interested people with online purchases and also with the recharge of the bonus purchased on their card," said project spokesman Martin Opatrny.
In addition to the library, it will also be possible to reload the electronic bonus on the Opencard in the automatic uploading machines located in some of the subway lobbys.
How are these uploading machines?
They are red, they remind us of a machine to pick up tickets, and the travelers will probably already be placed in them at the stations of the metro of Roztyly, Budjejovicka, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"Now there are in the city five but at the end of the year there would have to be eighty," Opatrny said.
The bonus is controlled by the machine instead of the driver
The use of the machine, which will start operating tomorrow, is simple.
Just enter in it the Opencard chip card and the previously paid bonus will only be loaded in it.
Electronic bonds since tomorrow are valid not only in the capital but also in its surroundings.
That is, in the coaches and bus lines from the 300 to 499 numbers that mainly use the inhabitants of the locations of central Bohemia.
"In the trains attached to the integrated transport of Prague, there are reviewers equipped with a reading card that will help confirm the validity of the time and zone of the bonus," explained the control of the tickets, Filip Drápal of the Ropid organization that sets the schedules for the collective transport of Prague.
The roundabout buses have their reading cards mounted on the driver's cab.
When entering, it is necessary not only to show the card to the driver but also to accompany it with the Opencard in the place intended for it on the side of the Box.
With this, the driver controls the validity of the bonus.
"If the passenger needs to verify the validity of the bonds, there is nothing easier than asking the driver for this information," Drápal said.
Passengers who do not travel on the round buses and do not remember when they finish their bonus validity can be sent to the forwarding machines where the cards are recharged.
Here, on the machine screen, you will see information about the validity of your document.
