Psychology of suppositions: Why do we spend more money?
The participants in the auctions are willing to spend more money and overestimate the product.
Neurologists and economists at the University of New York discovered the neurological bases - economics of this well-known and seemingly irrational behavior.
According to the study published in Science magazine, people don't want to lose in competitions such as eBay auctions, so they prefer to pay even an excessive price.
Scientists have tried to establish the neurological scheme of this "game" by means of experimental substations.
One of the volunteer groups played the lottery, the other participated in a auction and as long as the functional magnetic resonance system (fMRI) examined the active areas of the brain of the participants in the experiment.
In both games the participants could earn money, but during the auctions, where it is essential to bet more than the other, by losing the game, the operation of the complex called stratum located below the brain cortex was intensified.
This brain area, in addition to many other functions, plays a role in the "auto premium" mechanism of the nervous system.
Thus, according to scientists, the increase in bets is explained as a prevention against causing an intense reaction to the stratum.
In order to justify their theory, the economists of the scientific group also conducted a financial follow-up study.
In this experiment, three groups were betting on one person under different circumstances.
The control group was simply informed of the actual value of the product in question, and its members were betting.
Another group was also promised that if they won, they would receive $15 more.
On the other hand, the third group received exactly $15 before the auction, but in the event of the loss of the auction, the members of the group lost even that money.
So the only difference between the two groups was that for one the triumph was highlighted and for the other the failure.
However, checking the hypothesis of neurologists, the members of the group that played "against failure" were willing to bet even more than the members of the control group and the "winner" group.
"These results cannot be derived from any previously existing economic theory.
As those so far explained the phenomena of auctions only with the joy of winning and the prevention of risks.
Only visual neurological methods helped resolve this contradiction between the two theories, so that we now come to a third explanation" - established Andrew Schutter, professor of the Faculty of Economics at the University of New York.
Hepatitis: When should you go to your doctor?
In the world some 50 million people suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C, and in Hungary the chronic liver disease is considered one of the main causes of death.
The number of infected in this country is estimated to be 100 000, but only seven thousand are treated because many of the sick do not know that they are infected.
The name of hepatitis is the common name of different liver diseases caused by the virus.
Symptoms appear to be very much; liver infection and jaundice are characteristic, but their pathogens and diseases are very different.
Hepatitis virus depending on the pathogen agent is spread through two main forms: hepatitis A and E via food (e.g., contaminated water or food), hepatitis B, C, D and other viruses with blood and body humour (sperm, vaginal humour, saliva).
It is recommended that travellers be protected by a vaccine against the A and B virus, no vaccines against the C.
The symptoms of hepatitis A appear two or three weeks after consuming the food infected, it is manifested by a general condition, weakness, abdominal pain and nausea.
After this appear in the skin and in the white of the eyes, the excretion becomes clear, the urine of the dark color and the healing can last even for two to three weeks.
Each year, one million people die from cancer in the world and liver cirrhosis caused by hepatitis B, the most serious forms of this disease.
The main reason for this is that, according to the calculations, only one in 10 people is given pharmacological treatment.
Hepatitis C can also have very serious consequences: without treatment it can produce liver cirrhosis and even cancer.
Most people do not know that they are sick because this pathological agent gradually destroys the liver cells and often the first symptoms only appear 20-30 years later.
Therefore, early recognition, systematic medical control, is very important.
This disease is much more common in three groups: people who had blood transfusions before 1991, drug users and those who carry tattoos.
At present, there are some 200 million people in the world suffering from chronic hepatitis C.
As this disease can also be detected with routine laboratory control, it is worth consulting with the family doctor when experiencing any unknown symptoms.
The disease has healing if it is detected in time, it is possible to eliminate the virus from the body, thus it can eliminate the infection and prevent cancer.
It was the World Hepatitis Day on 30 September, which was organized for the first time in 2004 by organizations representing the sick.
Its aim is to draw attention to the causes of chronic liver infections caused by viruses and to the importance of their early recognition.
Does it hurt less those who believe in God?
According to a recent study, religious faith has a calming effect that also alleviated the death of the martyrs of Catholicism.
The scientists at Oxford University conducted an interesting experiment: they analyzed how religious belief affects human pain - reported the British Telegraph newspaper.
As part of this unique experiment, electrical shock was applied to 12 Catholic believers and to the same number of atheists, while everyone was looking at a painting of the Virgin Mary.
According to the results, Catholic believers were able to exclude most of their pain.
Thanks to the human brain scanning technique, it was possible to verify that the Catholic believers were able to activate that part of their brain that is responsible for the regulation of pain.
This experiment is the first of the series of research in which scientists, philosophers and theologians from the various departments of the University also participate.
The analysis took place the following way; they set up a sparking instrument at the patient's left hand, which applied the electrical shock.
The researchers asked the participants of the experiment to set their eyes on two paintings; the Virgin Mary, the work of the 17th century Sassoferrat and the Lady of the armion of Leonardo da Vinci of the 15th century.
The researchers had hoped that the Virgin Mary's show would produce a certain religious spirit among the faithful, as they chose Leonardo's oil because it was not too different from the other, and they thought it had a calming effect.
Patients spent half an hour in an MRI scanner, receiving 20 electrical shocks in four successive parts during that period while observing the painting of the religious theme or the other.
The Catholics said that when they looked at the Virgin Mary they felt "security" as "protected people", "they were calmed and in their hearts peace reigned."
When observing the religious theme, they felt about 12 percent less pain than when they looked at Leonardo's work.
The psychologist Miguel Farias, who also participated in the experiment, thinks that with any such impressive image you can achieve a similar effect with the atheists too, you just have to find the right image.
"We should find the portrait of a person who feels very positive, like a mother or a father," said the psychologist.
The Anglican bishop Tom Wright celebrated the outcome of the investigation.
"The exercise of faith should and in many cases should really change our personality" - added Wright.
After these formidable results there is only one question: What effect would pain control have on the faithful if the Lady of Leonardo or another painter of her size were shown to the faithful?
Would the vision of a high-quality Virgin Mary throw even better results?
